00:13:04,510 --> 00:13:08,228
Wait a minute, you mean they're using
him as a decoy to make an opening for them?

252
00:13:08,253 --> 00:13:12,168
Yup! Seems like they'll use the
confusion to send in the royal guard!

253
00:13:12,193 --> 00:13:13,140
"Seems like"?! But Lloyd...!

254
00:13:13,165 --> 00:13:14,104
Miss Cecile.

255
00:13:14,909 --> 00:13:17,127
I'm ready. Please let me do it.

256
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:19,259
If Lancelot and I are needed,

257
00:13:19,284 --> 00:13:23,490
and we're able to give the hostages an
opportunity to be saved, then I'll do it.

258
00:13:23,752 --> 00:13:25,627
Even if it means being a decoy.

259
00:13:37,394 --> 00:13:38,814
Warrant Officer Kururugi,

260
00:13:38,839 --> 00:13:40,458
here is a guideline for your mission.

261
00:13:40,483 --> 00:13:44,311
According to prime search, the hostages
are located on the hotel's middle floor

262
00:13:44,336 --> 00:13:46,883
and believed to be locked inside a food storage room.

263
00:13:46,944 --> 00:13:52,361
Advanced prototype weapon Z-01 Lancelot will
use the utilities tunnel to move under the hotel.

264
00:13:53,256 --> 00:13:56,862
Once on site, you will destroy the
foundation block and submerge the building.

265
00:13:57,133 --> 00:13:59,964
The area with the hostages
should hold out for eight minutes.

266
00:13:59,989 --> 00:14:03,618
Hostage rescue and mop-up of the
terrorists will be handled by other units.

267
00:14:03,643 --> 00:14:06,209
You will be using the VARIS to destroy the foundation.

268
00:14:06,353 --> 00:14:09,228
Set the impact rail to anti-material level three.

269
00:14:09,253 --> 00:14:13,413
The only variable in this is that pesky
linear cannon waiting for you in the tunnel.

270
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,792
Space is tight in there.

271
00:14:14,817 --> 00:14:18,401
The Lancelot will only have a 47.8% evasion rate.

272
00:14:18,426 --> 00:14:20,146
Are we really going through with this?

273
00:14:20,171 --> 00:14:23,189
Yup. Make sure you both pull
out of there before it's too late.

274
00:14:23,214 --> 00:14:25,893
Lancelot might be wrecked, that would be unacceptable.

275
00:14:25,918 --> 00:14:27,126
"Before it's too late"?

276
00:14:27,151 --> 00:14:28,429
Mmmm!

277
00:14:29,344 --> 00:14:30,753
Understood, sir.

278
00:14:31,253 --> 00:14:32,207
Suzaku.

279
00:14:32,232 --> 00:14:36,702
The president, and Nina and I are going
to Lake Kawaguchi on Sunday. Wanna join us?

280
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:39,232
Sorry. I have to work that day.

281
00:14:39,665 --> 00:14:40,661
You do?

282
00:14:40,816 --> 00:14:42,943
Too bad, but I guess that can't be helped then.

283
00:14:42,968 --> 00:14:44,416
But thank you for inviting me.

284
00:14:44,441 --> 00:14:45,941
I really appreciate it.

285
00:14:45,998 --> 00:14:47,821
I hope all of you have a great time.

286
00:14:48,719 --> 00:14:50,652
Twelve minutes to operation start.

287
00:14:50,677 --> 00:14:52,042
Commencing countdown.

288
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:56,830
An Eleven?

289
00:14:56,975 --> 00:14:58,308
What did you say?!

290
00:14:58,780 --> 00:15:01,535
Not Elevens! We are Japanese, dammit!

291
00:15:01,560 --> 00:15:03,810
Yes, we're aware of that! Just lay off of her!

292
00:15:03,835 --> 00:15:06,210
Then correct her! We're not called "Elevens"!

293
00:15:06,235 --> 00:15:07,459
Fine, we'll correct her!

294
00:15:07,484 --> 00:15:09,275
How dare you speak like that to me!

295
00:15:09,306 --> 00:15:13,389
You three, come with me to the next
room, and I'll teach you a real lesson!

296
00:15:16,426 --> 00:15:17,160
Mh-hm.

297
00:15:17,672 --> 00:15:19,692
I said get up! Now!

298
00:15:21,358 --> 00:15:22,826
Let me go!

299
00:15:22,851 --> 00:15:23,806
Stop it!

300
00:15:23,899 --> 00:15:25,534
Who the hell are you?!

301
00:15:26,190 --> 00:15:29,241
I demand you take me to your
leader right now, understand?!

302
00:15:29,266 --> 00:15:29,816
What?!

303
00:15:29,841 --> 00:15:31,223
No, Sub-viceroy, please.

304
00:15:31,248 --> 00:15:33,541
You're addressing Euphemia Li Britannia.

305
00:15:33,601 --> 00:15:36,271
The third princess of the Britannian Empire.

306
00:15:38,046 --> 00:15:41,407
Are you all right, young lady? You haven't been hurt?

307
00:15:42,108 --> 00:15:42,873
No.

308
00:15:43,841 --> 00:15:46,049
You have no intention of joining me?

309
00:15:46,140 --> 00:15:48,965
Remove that mask and reveal your real face to us.

310
00:15:48,990 --> 00:15:50,407
It's disrespectful not to.

311
00:15:50,432 --> 00:15:51,616
I understand.

312
00:15:51,641 --> 00:15:54,580
But before I do, I'd like to ask you something.

313
00:15:54,618 --> 00:15:57,850
What exactly do you hope to accomplish by this action?

314
00:15:57,875 --> 00:15:58,902
Gain attention.

315
00:15:59,006 --> 00:16:02,747
I want this country and the world to
know that the Japanese aren't dead yet.

316
00:16:02,772 --> 00:16:03,897
How stale.

317
00:16:03,922 --> 00:16:04,523
Hm?!

318
00:16:04,620 --> 00:16:08,284
You people are obsolete. There's no saving you.

319
00:16:08,309 --> 00:16:10,142
What?! Why you arrogant...!

320
00:16:10,167 --> 00:16:12,347
Explain what you mean by that, Zero.

321
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:15,041
M.E. boost...

322
00:16:15,066 --> 00:16:16,686
Lancelot, now launching!

323
00:16:19,219 --> 00:16:21,219
Reaction confirmed! One enemy Knightmare!

324
00:16:21,244 --> 00:16:23,054
It moves twice as fast as the others!

325
00:16:23,079 --> 00:16:25,199
So what?! It'll end up like the rest!

326
00:16:25,224 --> 00:16:28,879
Super electromagnetic shrapnel cannon... Fire!

327
00:16:37,015 --> 00:16:38,972
I warned you about this, Lloyd!

328
00:16:38,997 --> 00:16:42,269
He doesn't want to play decoy, he's going for the gold!

329
00:16:45,847 --> 00:16:49,538
I brought the hostage that I radioed about
earlier for the lieutenant colonel to see.

330
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:51,635
She claims that she's Princess Euphemia.

331
00:16:52,244 --> 00:16:53,078
Zero!

332
00:16:53,312 --> 00:16:55,943
There's no point talking any more!

333
00:16:55,968 --> 00:16:56,600
Die.

334
00:16:58,851 --> 00:16:59,753
Fire!

335
00:17:06,261 --> 00:17:07,086
Colonel!

336
00:17:08,479 --> 00:17:09,799
Calm yourselves.

337
00:17:10,697 --> 00:17:11,453
Zero.

338
00:17:11,506 --> 00:17:16,741
The colonel and the others committed suicide when
they realized how meaningless this operation was.

339
00:17:17,486 --> 00:17:18,491
Euphemia...

340
00:17:18,865 --> 00:17:21,961
You were willing to sacrifice yourself for the commoners.

341
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:23,440
You haven't changed.

342
00:17:23,515 --> 00:17:23,998
Uh?

343
00:17:24,023 --> 00:17:26,364
What? The ASEEC's Knightmare?

344
00:17:26,389 --> 00:17:29,175
Yes. At the rate it's going, it'll break through soon.

345
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:31,616
Huh. Do we dare hold out hope?

346
00:17:33,615 --> 00:17:36,484
Yes! It can take this level of destructive force!

347
00:17:37,732 --> 00:17:39,535
That thing broke through salvo number five!

348
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:40,597
I can't believe it!

349
00:17:40,622 --> 00:17:41,698
Just don't panic!

350
00:17:41,723 --> 00:17:44,613
Deploy the quad-link free-fire arm gun, batteries too!

351
00:17:44,638 --> 00:17:47,066
We'll shield this final defense line with our lives!

352
00:17:47,151 --> 00:17:49,431
Miss Cecile, it's time for me to use the VARIS.

353
00:17:49,456 --> 00:17:50,751
No, you could get killed!

354
00:17:52,516 --> 00:17:54,308
There's no room for me to evade.

355
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:56,769
I'll risk getting blasted to take the first shot!

356
00:18:02,688 --> 00:18:04,829
Why, you stinking son of a...

357
00:18:05,630 --> 00:18:08,539
I heard that you're the sub-viceroy now, Your Highness.

358
00:18:08,564 --> 00:18:10,749
Princess Euphemia Li Britannia.

359
00:18:10,774 --> 00:18:12,796
It's not an appointment I'm happy with.

360
00:18:12,821 --> 00:18:15,820
No. That's because Clovis was murdered.

361
00:18:15,982 --> 00:18:17,686
That was my handiwork.

362
00:18:18,521 --> 00:18:21,400
He begged pathetically for his life to the very end.

363
00:18:21,655 --> 00:18:24,879
He pleaded with the same tongue
that ordered the deaths of Elevens.

364
00:18:24,904 --> 00:18:27,353
So is that the reason why you killed my brother?

365
00:18:27,565 --> 00:18:28,394
No.

366
00:18:28,419 --> 00:18:29,410
Then why?!

367
00:18:29,848 --> 00:18:33,549
Because Clovis was an offspring of the Britannian emperor.

368
00:18:33,838 --> 00:18:35,400
That reminds me...

369
00:18:35,517 --> 00:18:37,974
You're one of his children, too, aren't you?

370
00:18:38,066 --> 00:18:39,436
Use maximum output!

371
00:18:39,461 --> 00:18:41,868
I don't give a damn if that destroys the guns!

372
00:18:41,893 --> 00:18:45,891
Be prepared to die defending this spot! Smash him!

373
00:19:00,293 --> 00:19:01,468
It's the Eleven...

374
00:19:13,453 --> 00:19:15,043
He really did it!

375
00:19:15,169 --> 00:19:16,074
Guilford!

376
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:16,906
Right!

377
00:19:19,691 --> 00:19:20,825
No way!

378
00:19:23,765 --> 00:19:25,579
The white Knightmare from before!

379
00:19:30,060 --> 00:19:31,721
Euphy!

380
00:19:32,162 --> 00:19:33,449
My friends!

381
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:35,967
Warrant Officer Kururugi, don't!

382
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:41,132
What about the cameras in van three?

383
00:19:41,157 --> 00:19:42,510
I told you, Zero took the van...

384
00:19:42,535 --> 00:19:45,111
Well then, let's hope we pick up a signal from them!

385
00:19:45,285 --> 00:19:47,182
What're you doing, Zero?

386
00:19:47,568 --> 00:19:51,270
Wasn't that part of your plan? To show us something?

387
00:19:59,588 --> 00:20:00,679
He's all right!

388
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:09,543
I couldn't rescue them.

389
00:20:11,072 --> 00:20:12,193
They're dead.

390
00:20:12,524 --> 00:20:13,622
I failed.

391
00:20:14,007 --> 00:20:15,611
Not again!

392
00:20:20,809 --> 00:20:21,695
We've got it!

393
00:20:24,588 --> 00:20:27,656
My dear Britannians, have no fear.

394
00:20:27,834 --> 00:20:31,121
All of the hostages from the hotel are safe and sound.

395
00:20:31,505 --> 00:20:34,599
I, Zero, return them to you unharmed.

396
00:20:35,940 --> 00:20:36,938
They're fine!

397
00:20:36,997 --> 00:20:38,044
They're all right!

398
00:20:38,096 --> 00:20:40,266
Of all the brazen audacity!

399
00:20:40,397 --> 00:20:44,446
If we attack you, those people will
quickly become your hostages, won't they?!

400
00:20:47,605 --> 00:20:48,423
People!

401
00:20:48,794 --> 00:20:51,919
Fear us, or rally behind us, as you see fit.

402
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:54,631
We... are the Black Knights!

403
00:20:54,784 --> 00:20:55,909
Black Knights?

404
00:20:56,030 --> 00:20:57,431
Ironic, isn't it?

405
00:20:57,456 --> 00:21:00,101
The terrorists referring to themselves as knights.

406
00:21:00,126 --> 00:21:03,932
We of the Black Knights stand with
all those who have no weapons to wield!

407
00:21:04,212 --> 00:21:08,532
Regardless of whether they be Elevens... or Britannians!

408
00:21:08,751 --> 00:21:13,356
The Japan Liberation Front cowardly
took innocent Britannian civilians hostage

409
00:21:13,381 --> 00:21:15,639
and then mercilessly executed them.

410
00:21:16,008 --> 00:21:18,425
It was a wanton and meaningless act.

411
00:21:18,545 --> 00:21:20,280
Therefore, they have been punished.

412
00:21:20,316 --> 00:21:21,200
Uh?

413
00:21:21,486 --> 00:21:23,792
You heard me right! I said let it run!

414
00:21:24,213 --> 00:21:27,290
Liable?! I'll be the one responsible for this!

415
00:21:27,315 --> 00:21:32,524
Just as former viceroy Clovis was punished for
ordering the slaughter of countless unarmed Elevens.

416
00:21:32,853 --> 00:21:36,423
We could not stand by and allow
such cruelty to be carried out.

417
00:21:36,511 --> 00:21:38,910
And so, we made him pay for his actions.

418
00:21:39,049 --> 00:21:42,244
I will not repudiate battle on a fair and level field.

419
00:21:42,269 --> 00:21:46,900
But neither will I tolerate a one-sided
massacre of the weak by the strong!

420
00:21:46,976 --> 00:21:48,639
The only ones who should kill...

421
00:21:48,664 --> 00:21:51,034
...are those of us who are prepared to be killed!

422
00:21:51,405 --> 00:21:55,230
Wherever oppressors abuse their power
by attacking those who are powerless,

423
00:21:55,335 --> 00:21:56,803
we shall appear again!

424
00:21:56,979 --> 00:22:00,239
No matter how mighty... how formidable our foe may be!

425
00:22:01,421 --> 00:22:03,830
Knights... for justice?

426
00:22:05,421 --> 00:22:08,295
Those of you with power... fear us!

427
00:22:08,543 --> 00:22:11,794
Those of you without it... rally behind us!

428
00:22:11,868 --> 00:22:17,055
We, the Black Knights, shall be the
ones who stand in judgment of this world!

429
00:23:49,597 --> 00:23:50,722
I was lucky.

430
00:23:50,830 --> 00:23:52,897
Heaven must truly be on my side.

431
00:23:53,265 --> 00:23:56,943
I never expected that Cornelia's
one weakness was among the hostages.

432
00:23:57,188 --> 00:23:58,913
A weakness named Euphemia.

433
00:23:59,052 --> 00:24:02,626
From now on, the Black Knights
shall become my counterattack.

434
00:24:02,732 --> 00:24:04,857
Against the world in which I was trapped.

435
00:24:04,931 --> 00:24:07,033
And against my own undecided heart.

